1Ô∏è‚É£ Creating a table with PRIMARY KEY
Q1. Create a Students table with student_id as PRIMARY KEY.
Answer
sql
CREATE TABLE Students (
    student_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    age INT
);
2Ô∏è‚É£ Adding NOT NULL constraint
Q2. Create an Employees table where name and salary cannot be NULL.
Answer
sql
CREATE TABLE Employees (
    emp_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    salary DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL
);
3Ô∏è‚É£ UNIQUE constraint
Q3. Ensure each employee has a unique email.
Answer
sql
CREATE TABLE EmployeeDetails (
    emp_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE,
    phone VARCHAR(20)
);
4Ô∏è‚É£ CHECK constraint
Q4. Create a table where age must be greater than 18.
Answer
sql
CREATE TABLE Users (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    age INT CHECK (age > 18)
);
5Ô∏è‚É£ DEFAULT constraint
Q5. Create a products table where default quantity is 1.
Answer
sql
CREATE TABLE Products (
    product_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100),
    quantity INT DEFAULT 1
);
6Ô∏è‚É£ FOREIGN KEY constraint
Q6. Create an Orders table where customer_id references Customers table.
Answer
sql
CREATE TABLE Orders (
    order_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    order_date DATE,
    customer_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES Customers(customer_id)
);
7Ô∏è‚É£ Adding a constraint AFTER table creation
Q7. Add a UNIQUE constraint to the phone column in EmployeeDetails.
Answer
sql
ALTER TABLE EmployeeDetails
ADD CONSTRAINT unique_phone UNIQUE (phone);
8Ô∏è‚É£ Dropping a constraint
Q8. Remove the UNIQUE constraint on phone added earlier.
Answer
sql
ALTER TABLE EmployeeDetails
DROP CONSTRAINT unique_phone;
(Name varies by SQL engine)

9Ô∏è‚É£ Using ON DELETE CASCADE
Q9. Create Orders table where deleting a customer deletes their orders automatically.
Answer
sql
CREATE TABLE Orders (
    order_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT,
    amount DECIMAL(10,2),
    FOREIGN KEY (customer_id)
    REFERENCES Customers(customer_id)
    ON DELETE CASCADE
);
üîü Composite PRIMARY KEY
Q10. Create a table Enrollments with composite key (student_id, course_id).
Answer
sql
CREATE TABLE Enrollments (
    student_id INT,
    course_id INT,
    enroll_date DATE,
    PRIMARY KEY (student_id, course_id)
);
